</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">To emphasise the anterior gonopod showing a scalloped and shield-shaped coxosternum.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
Differs from congeners of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Diplopoda" family="Cambalopsidae" genus="Glyphiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glyphiulus formosus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Glyphiulus formosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group by both ♂ femora 6 and 7 being slightly inflated and the anterior gonopod without apicomesal process, as well as the posterior gonopod with less than ten microspinules. Based on molecular evidence, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. scutatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="scutatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">G. scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. differs from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1847" class="Diplopoda" family="Cambalopsidae" genus="Glyphiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glyphiulus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Glyphiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species analysed in a&gt; 15.8% uncorrected p-distance of the COI barcoding gene.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
Length of both sexes ca. 25.0-41.0 mm, mid-body rings round in cross-section, their width and height similar, 1.3-1.8 (♂) or 1.8-2.0 mm (♀). Body with 55-68 podous + 1-4 apodous rings + telson. Colouration purple-brownish to dark brownish, legs light brownish to almost transparent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pictures of live animals A G. sinuatoprocessus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Niubi Yan B G. scutatus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Bianfu Dong C G. portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Baiyan Dong D G. xiniudong Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Xiniu Dong E G. conuliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov. from Cave Yanzi Dong." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705255" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Head</emphasis>
surface smooth. Labrum with four teeth anteromedially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Glyphiulus scutatus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype from Cave Napang Dong A gnathochilarium and right antenna B antenna tip C leg 3, frontal view D leg 1, frontal view E ♀ paratype, vulvae F penes G, J posterior gonopod, frontal and caudal views, respectively H mid-body leg and claw I anterior gonopods, caudal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, H), 0.2 mm (B-E), 0.1 mm (F, G, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705263" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">13A</figureCitation>
). Ocellaria blackish, with 8-12 ommatidia arranged in two irregular linear rows (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Glyphiulus scutatus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype from Cave Napang Dong A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705262" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">12B</figureCitation>
). Antennae short, slightly clavate, reaching back to ring 3; in length, antennomeres 5&gt; 3&gt; 4&gt; 2&gt; 6&gt; 1&gt; 7. Antennomeres 5-7 each with a distodorsal field or corolla of bacilliform sensilla (sensory bacilli). Antennomere 7 with four sensory cones (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Glyphiulus scutatus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype from Cave Napang Dong A gnathochilarium and right antenna B antenna tip C leg 3, frontal view D leg 1, frontal view E ♀ paratype, vulvae F penes G, J posterior gonopod, frontal and caudal views, respectively H mid-body leg and claw I anterior gonopods, caudal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, H), 0.2 mm (B-E), 0.1 mm (F, G, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705263" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">13B</figureCitation>
). Gnathochilarium with a separate promentum, setae variable in number, polytrichous or smooth on promentum and mentum, lamellae linguales each with 4-6 setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Glyphiulus scutatus Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype from Cave Napang Dong A gnathochilarium and right antenna B antenna tip C leg 3, frontal view D leg 1, frontal view E ♀ paratype, vulvae F penes G, J posterior gonopod, frontal and caudal views, respectively H mid-body leg and claw I anterior gonopods, caudal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, H), 0.2 mm (B-E), 0.1 mm (F, G, I, J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705263" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">13A</figureCitation>
). Mandible not dissected.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705262" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" start="Figure 12" startId="F12">
